            content:
                "# SQS, SNS, Kinesis & EventBridge Reference\n\n## SQS — Simple Queue Service\n\n### Types\n\n| Feature | Standard | FIFO |\n|---------|----------|------|\n| Throughput | Unlimited | 300 msg/s (3000 batched) |\n| Ordering | Best-effort | Strict within MessageGroupId |\n| Delivery | At-least-once | Exactly-once |\n| Name | Any | Must end with `.fifo` |\n\n### CDK\n\n```typescript\nconst dlq = new sqs.Queue(this, 'MyDLQ', {\n  queueName: `${props.stage}-my-dlq`,\n  retentionPeriod: Duration.days(14),\n});\n\nconst queue = new sqs.Queue(this, 'MyQueue', {\n  queueName: `${props.stage}-my-queue`,\n  visibilityTimeout: Duration.seconds(180), // ≥ 6× Lambda timeout\n  retentionPeriod: Duration.days(7),\n  deadLetterQueue: { queue: dlq, maxReceiveCount: 3 },\n});\n\nconst fifoQueue = new sqs.Queue(this, 'OrderQueue', {\n  queueName: `${props.stage}-orders.fifo`,\n  fifo: true,\n  contentBasedDeduplication: true,\n  deduplicationScope: sqs.DeduplicationScope.MESSAGE_GROUP,\n  fifoThroughputLimit: sqs.FifoThroughputLimit.PER_MESSAGE_GROUP_ID,\n  visibilityTimeout: Duration.seconds(180),\n  deadLetterQueue: { queue: fifoDlq, maxReceiveCount: 3 },\n});\n\nmyFunction.addEventSource(new lambdaEventSources.SqsEventSource(queue, {\n  batchSize: 10,\n  maxBatchingWindow: Duration.seconds(5),\n  reportBatchItemFailures: true, // CRITICAL\n}));\n```\n\n### Sending Messages\n\n```typescript\nimport { SQSClient, SendMessageCommand, SendMessageBatchCommand } from '@aws-sdk/client-sqs';\n\nconst sqs = new SQSClient({});\n\nawait sqs.send(new SendMessageCommand({\n  QueueUrl: process.env.QUEUE_URL!,\n  MessageBody: JSON.stringify({ orderId: '123', action: 'process' }),\n  DelaySeconds: 10,\n  MessageAttributes: {\n    eventType: { DataType: 'String', StringValue: 'ORDER_CREATED' },\n  },\n}));\n\n// FIFO\nawait sqs.send(new SendMessageCommand({\n  QueueUrl: process.env.FIFO_QUEUE_URL!,\n  MessageBody: JSON.stringify({ orderId: '123' }),\n  MessageGroupId: 'order-123',\n  MessageDeduplicationId: 'unique-id-123',\n}));\n\n// Batch (up to 10)\nawait sqs.send(new SendMessageBatchCommand({\n  QueueUrl: process.env.QUEUE_URL!,\n  Entries: items.map((item, i) => ({ Id: `msg-${i}`, MessageBody: JSON.stringify(item) })),\n}));\n```\n\n### Typical Mistakes\n\n1. **Visibility timeout too short** → message processed twice.\n2. **Not enabling `reportBatchItemFailures`** → one poison message blocks batch.\n3. **SNS→SQS format**: payload is `JSON.parse(record.body).Message`, not `record.body`.\n4. **FIFO name**: must end with `.fifo`.\n5. **DLQ type mismatch**: Standard DLQ for Standard, FIFO for FIFO.\n\n---\n\n## SNS — Simple Notification Service\n\n### Purpose\nPub/sub. One message → many subscribers. Fan-out.\n\n### CDK\n\n```typescript\nconst topic = new sns.Topic(this, 'OrderEventsTopic', {\n  topicName: `${props.stage}-order-events`,\n});\n\ntopic.addSubscription(new snsSubscriptions.SqsSubscription(queue, {\n  rawMessageDelivery: true, // delivers body directly\n  filterPolicy: {\n    eventType: sns.SubscriptionFilter.stringFilter({ allowlist: ['ORDER_CREATED'] }),\n    amount: sns.SubscriptionFilter.numericFilter({ greaterThan: 100 }),\n  },\n}));\n\ntopic.grantPublish(myLambda);\n```\n\n### Publishing\n\n```typescript\nimport { SNSClient, PublishCommand } from '@aws-sdk/client-sns';\n\nawait new SNSClient({}).send(new PublishCommand({\n  TopicArn: process.env.TOPIC_ARN!,\n  Message: JSON.stringify({ orderId: '123', total: 150 }),\n  MessageAttributes: {\n    eventType: { DataType: 'String', StringValue: 'ORDER_CREATED' },\n    amount: { DataType: 'Number', StringValue: '150' },\n  },\n}));\n```\n\n### SNS→SQS Message Parsing\n\n```typescript\n// rawMessageDelivery: false (default) — wrapped in SNS envelope:\nconst snsMessage = JSON.parse(record.body);\nconst actualPayload = JSON.parse(snsMessage.Message);\n\n// rawMessageDelivery: true — direct:\nconst actualPayload = JSON.parse(record.body);\n```\n\n### Key Rule\nUse `rawMessageDelivery: true` for SQS subscriptions to avoid double-parsing.\n\n---\n\n## Kinesis\n\n### Purpose\nReal-time streaming. 1MB/s write, 2MB/s read per shard. Ordered within shard. Retention 24h–365 days.\n\n### When to Use\n\n| Use Case | Service |\n|----------|---------|\n| Real-time analytics, log aggregation | **Kinesis** |\n| Task queue, decoupled processing | **SQS** |\n| Event-driven routing, multiple targets | **EventBridge** |\n| Replay from a point in time | **Kinesis** |\n\n### CDK\n\n```typescript\nconst stream = new kinesis.Stream(this, 'EventStream', {\n  streamName: `${props.stage}-events`,\n  streamMode: kinesis.StreamMode.ON_DEMAND,\n  retentionPeriod: Duration.hours(72),\n});\n\nmyFunction.addEventSource(new lambdaEventSources.KinesisEventSource(stream, {\n  startingPosition: lambda.StartingPosition.TRIM_HORIZON,\n  batchSize: 100,\n  maxBatchingWindow: Duration.seconds(5),\n  parallelizationFactor: 10,\n  retryAttempts: 3,\n  bisectBatchOnError: true,\n  onFailure: new lambdaEventSources.SqsDestination(dlq),\n  reportBatchItemFailures: true,\n}));\n```\n\n### Producing\n\n```typescript\nimport { KinesisClient, PutRecordsCommand } from '@aws-sdk/client-kinesis';\n\nawait new KinesisClient({}).send(new PutRecordsCommand({\n  StreamName: process.env.STREAM_NAME!,\n  Records: events.map(e => ({\n    Data: Buffer.from(JSON.stringify(e)),\n    PartitionKey: e.userId, // same key → same shard → ordered\n  })),\n}));\n```\n\n---\n\n## EventBridge\n\n### Purpose\nServerless event bus. Schema-based filtering. 30+ native targets. Archive & replay.\n\n### CDK\n\n```typescript\nconst bus = new events.EventBus(this, 'AppEventBus', {\n  eventBusName: `${props.stage}-app-events`,\n});\n\nbus.archive('AllEventsArchive', {\n  archiveName: `${props.stage}-all-events`,\n  retention: Duration.days(90),\n  eventPattern: { account: [this.account] },\n});\n\nnew events.Rule(this, 'OrderCreatedRule', {\n  eventBus: bus,\n  eventPattern: {\n    source: ['com.myapp.orders'],\n    detailType: ['OrderCreated'],\n    detail: {\n      amount: [{ numeric: ['>', 100] }],\n      status: ['CONFIRMED'],\n      region: [{ prefix: 'us-' }],\n    },\n  },\n  targets: [\n    new targets.LambdaFunction(processOrderFn, {\n      retryAttempts: 2,\n      deadLetterQueue: dlq,\n    }),\n    new targets.SqsQueue(auditQueue),\n  ],\n});\n\n// Cron\nnew events.Rule(this, 'DailyCleanup', {\n  schedule: events.Schedule.cron({ minute: '0', hour: '2' }),\n  targets: [new targets.LambdaFunction(cleanupFn)],\n});\n```\n\n### Publishing\n\n```typescript\nimport { EventBridgeClient, PutEventsCommand } from '@aws-sdk/client-eventbridge';\n\nconst resp = await new EventBridgeClient({}).send(new PutEventsCommand({\n  Entries: [{\n    EventBusName: process.env.EVENT_BUS_NAME!,\n    Source: 'com.myapp.orders',\n    DetailType: 'OrderCreated',\n    Detail: JSON.stringify({ orderId: '123', amount: 250, status: 'CONFIRMED' }),\n    Time: new Date(),\n  }],\n}));\n// Check resp.FailedEntryCount > 0\n```\n\n### Filter Pattern Reference\n\n```typescript\n{ status: ['ACTIVE'] }                              // exact\n{ status: ['ACTIVE', 'PENDING'] }                    // OR\n{ region: [{ prefix: 'us-' }] }                      // prefix\n{ amount: [{ numeric: ['>', 100] }] }                // numeric\n{ amount: [{ numeric: ['>=', 10, '<=', 100] }] }    // between\n{ status: [{ 'anything-but': ['DELETED'] }] }        // not\n{ email: [{ exists: true }] }                         // exists\n```\n\n### EventBridge vs SNS\n\n| Feature | EventBridge | SNS |\n|---------|-------------|-----|\n| Filtering | Rich content-based | Message attributes |\n| Targets | 30+ services | Lambda, SQS, HTTP, email |\n| Archive & replay | Yes | No |\n| Schema discovery | Yes | No |\n\nUse EventBridge for complex routing. Use SNS for simple fan-out.\n",
