            path: 'references/cloudwatch-ssm-logging.md',
            role: 'reference',
            content:
                '# CloudWatch, Alarms, Logs Insights & SSM Reference\n\n## CloudWatch Logs\n\n### Structure\n```\nLog Group: /aws/lambda/my-function\n  └─ Log Stream: 2024/01/15/[$LATEST]abc123\n       └─ Log Events: timestamp + message\n```\n\n### CDK\n\n```typescript\nconst logGroup = new logs.LogGroup(this, \'MyFunctionLogs\', {\n  logGroupName: `/aws/lambda/${myFunction.functionName}`,\n  retention: logs.RetentionDays.TWO_WEEKS, // DEFAULT IS NEVER EXPIRE\n  removalPolicy: RemovalPolicy.DESTROY,\n});\n\n// Metric filter\nconst errorMetric = new logs.MetricFilter(this, \'ErrorFilter\', {\n  logGroup,\n  metricNamespace: \'MyApp\',\n  metricName: \'ErrorCount\',\n  filterPattern: logs.FilterPattern.literal(\'ERROR\'),\n  metricValue: \'1\',\n});\n```\n\n### Structured Logging — TypeScript Lambda\n\n```typescript\nconst logger = {\n  info: (message: string, data?: Record<string, any>) =>\n    console.log(JSON.stringify({ level: \'INFO\', message, ...data, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() })),\n  error: (message: string, error?: Error, data?: Record<string, any>) =>\n    console.error(JSON.stringify({\n      level: \'ERROR\', message, errorName: error?.name, errorMessage: error?.message,\n      stack: error?.stack, ...data, timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    })),\n};\n```\n\n### Structured Logging — Java ECS\n\n```java\n// Use SLF4J + logstash-logback-encoder\nimport static net.logstash.logback.argument.StructuredArguments.*;\n\nlog.info("Processing order", kv("orderId", orderId), kv("action", "START"));\nlog.error("Failed", kv("orderId", orderId), e);\n```\n\n```xml\n<!-- logback.xml -->\n<configuration>\n  <appender name="STDOUT" class="ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender">\n    <encoder class="net.logstash.logback.encoder.LogstashEncoder"/>\n  </appender>\n  <root level="INFO"><appender-ref ref="STDOUT"/></root>\n</configuration>\n```\n\n## CloudWatch Logs Insights\n\n### Essential Queries\n\n```sql\n-- Errors in last hour\nfields @timestamp, @message | filter @message like /ERROR/ | sort @timestamp desc | limit 100\n\n-- Structured JSON errors\nfields @timestamp, level, message, orderId, duration\n| filter level = "ERROR" | sort @timestamp desc | limit 50\n\n-- Error aggregation\nfields errorMessage | filter level = "ERROR"\n| stats count(*) as cnt by errorMessage | sort cnt desc\n\n-- P95 latency\nfields duration | filter message = "Processing completed"\n| stats avg(duration), pct(duration, 95) as p95, pct(duration, 99) as p99, max(duration) by bin(5m)\n\n-- Lambda cold starts\nfilter @type = "REPORT" | filter ispresent(@initDuration)\n| stats count() as coldStarts, avg(@initDuration) as avgColdStart by bin(1h)\n\n-- Lambda memory utilization\nfilter @type = "REPORT"\n| fields @maxMemoryUsed / @memorySize * 100 as memPct\n| filter memPct > 90 | sort memPct desc\n\n-- Find specific request\nfields @timestamp, @message | filter @requestId = "abc-123-def" | sort @timestamp asc\n\n-- ECS errors\nfields @timestamp, @message, @logStream\n| filter @logStream like /ecs/ | filter @message like /Exception|ERROR|FATAL/\n| sort @timestamp desc | limit 200\n```\n\n## CloudWatch Alarms\n\n### CDK\n\n```typescript\n// Lambda errors\nnew cloudwatch.Alarm(this, \'LambdaErrorAlarm\', {\n  metric: myFunction.metricErrors({ period: Duration.minutes(5), statistic: \'Sum\' }),\n  threshold: 5,\n  evaluationPeriods: 2,\n  datapointsToAlarm: 2,\n  treatMissingData: cloudwatch.TreatMissingData.NOT_BREACHING,\n}).addAlarmAction(new cw_actions.SnsAction(alertTopic));\n\n// Lambda throttles\nnew cloudwatch.Alarm(this, \'ThrottleAlarm\', {\n  metric: myFunction.metricThrottles({ period: Duration.minutes(1) }),\n  threshold: 1, evaluationPeriods: 1,\n  treatMissingData: cloudwatch.TreatMissingData.NOT_BREACHING,\n}).addAlarmAction(new cw_actions.SnsAction(alertTopic));\n\n// DLQ (any message = bad)\nnew cloudwatch.Alarm(this, \'DLQAlarm\', {\n  metric: dlq.metricApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible({ period: Duration.minutes(1) }),\n  threshold: 0,\n  comparisonOperator: cloudwatch.ComparisonOperator.GREATER_THAN_THRESHOLD,\n  evaluationPeriods: 1,\n}).addAlarmAction(new cw_actions.SnsAction(alertTopic));\n\n// SQS queue depth\nnew cloudwatch.Alarm(this, \'QueueDepthAlarm\', {\n  metric: queue.metricApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible({ period: Duration.minutes(5) }),\n  threshold: 1000, evaluationPeriods: 3,\n}).addAlarmAction(new cw_actions.SnsAction(alertTopic));\n\n// ECS CPU\nnew cloudwatch.Alarm(this, \'EcsCpuAlarm\', {\n  metric: ecsService.metricCpuUtilization({ period: Duration.minutes(5) }),\n  threshold: 80, evaluationPeriods: 3,\n}).addAlarmAction(new cw_actions.SnsAction(alertTopic));\n```\n\n### Key Metrics to Monitor\n\n| Service | Metric | Alert When |\n|---------|--------|------------|\n| Lambda | Errors | Any non-zero |\n| Lambda | Throttles | Hitting limit |\n| Lambda | Duration p95/p99 | Near timeout |\n| Lambda | IteratorAge | Consumer behind |\n| SQS | ApproxNumberOfMessagesVisible | Queue growing |\n| SQS | ApproxAgeOfOldestMessage | Processing delay |\n| SQS DLQ | ApproxNumberOfMessages | > 0 |\n| DynamoDB | ThrottledRequests | Being throttled |\n| ECS | CPUUtilization | > 80% |\n| ECS | MemoryUtilization | OOM risk |\n| ECS | RunningTaskCount | Below desired |\n\n---\n\n## SSM — Systems Manager Parameter Store\n\n### Purpose\nCentralized config and secrets. Hierarchical naming.\n\n### SSM vs Secrets Manager\n\n| Feature | SSM Parameter Store | Secrets Manager |\n|---------|-------------------|-----------------|\n| Cost | Free (standard) | $0.40/secret/month |\n| Max size | 4KB / 8KB | 64KB |\n| Rotation | Manual | Built-in |\n| Use for | Config, flags, endpoints | DB passwords, API keys |\n\n### CDK\n\n```typescript\nnew ssm.StringParameter(this, \'ApiEndpoint\', {\n  parameterName: `/${props.stage}/myapp/api-endpoint`,\n  stringValue: \'https://api.example.com\',\n});\n\n// Reference at deploy time\nconst val = ssm.StringParameter.valueForStringParameter(this, `/${props.stage}/myapp/api-endpoint`);\n\n// Reference at runtime — pass name, fetch in code\nenvironment: { DB_PASSWORD_PARAM: `/${props.stage}/myapp/db-password` }\n```\n\n### SDK\n\n```typescript\nimport { SSMClient, GetParameterCommand, GetParametersByPathCommand } from \'@aws-sdk/client-ssm\';\n\nconst ssm = new SSMClient({});\n\nconst { Parameter } = await ssm.send(new GetParameterCommand({\n  Name: `/${process.env.STAGE}/myapp/api-key`,\n  WithDecryption: true,\n}));\n\nconst { Parameters } = await ssm.send(new GetParametersByPathCommand({\n  Path: `/${process.env.STAGE}/myapp/`, Recursive: true, WithDecryption: true,\n}));\n```\n\n### Java\n\n```java\nSsmClient ssm = SsmClient.create();\nString val = ssm.getParameter(GetParameterRequest.builder()\n    .name("/" + stage + "/myapp/db-url").withDecryption(true).build()\n).parameter().value();\n```\n\n### DOs and DONTs\n\n| DO | DON\'T |\n|----|-------|\n| Use `/{stage}/{app}/{param}` naming | Flat names |\n| Use `SecureString` for secrets | Plain `String` for passwords |\n| Cache in Lambda global scope | Fetch every invocation |\n| Use `GetParametersByPath` | 20 separate `GetParameter` calls |\n',
