            path: 'references/ecs-fargate-containers.md',
            role: 'reference',
            content:
                "# ECS, Fargate & Containers Reference\n\n## Concepts\n\n| Concept | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Cluster** | Logical grouping of tasks/services |\n| **Task Definition** | Blueprint: image, CPU, memory, ports, IAM role |\n| **Task** | Running instance of a task definition |\n| **Service** | Maintains desired task count, ALB integration |\n\n## EC2 vs Fargate\n\n| Feature | EC2 | Fargate |\n|---------|-----|---------|\n| Infrastructure | You manage | AWS managed |\n| Cost | Cheaper for steady high utilization | Pay per task |\n| GPU | Yes | Limited |\n| SSH | Yes | No (use ECS Exec) |\n| Best for | Cost optimization | Most workloads |\n\n## CDK — Fargate Service (Java)\n\n```typescript\nconst vpc = new ec2.Vpc(this, 'Vpc', {\n  maxAzs: 2,\n  natGateways: 1, // $32/month each — use 1 for non-prod\n});\n\nconst cluster = new ecs.Cluster(this, 'Cluster', {\n  clusterName: `${props.stage}-cluster`,\n  vpc,\n  containerInsights: true,\n});\n\nconst taskDef = new ecs.FargateTaskDefinition(this, 'TaskDef', {\n  memoryLimitMiB: 1024,\n  cpu: 512,\n  runtimePlatform: {\n    cpuArchitecture: ecs.CpuArchitecture.ARM64,\n    operatingSystemFamily: ecs.OperatingSystemFamily.LINUX,\n  },\n});\n\nmyTable.grantReadWriteData(taskDef.taskRole);\n\nconst logGroup = new logs.LogGroup(this, 'ServiceLogs', {\n  logGroupName: `/ecs/${props.stage}/my-service`,\n  retention: logs.RetentionDays.TWO_WEEKS,\n});\n\ntaskDef.addContainer('App', {\n  image: ecs.ContainerImage.fromEcrRepository(repo, props.imageTag),\n  logging: ecs.LogDrivers.awsLogs({ logGroup, streamPrefix: 'app' }),\n  environment: {\n    STAGE: props.stage,\n    TABLE_NAME: myTable.tableName,\n    JAVA_OPTS: '-Xms256m -Xmx768m -XX:+UseG1GC',\n  },\n  secrets: {\n    DB_PASSWORD: ecs.Secret.fromSsmParameter(dbPasswordParam),\n  },\n  healthCheck: {\n    command: ['CMD-SHELL', 'curl -f http://localhost:8080/actuator/health || exit 1'],\n    interval: Duration.seconds(30),\n    timeout: Duration.seconds(5),\n    retries: 3,\n    startPeriod: Duration.seconds(60),\n  },\n  portMappings: [{ containerPort: 8080 }],\n});\n\nconst service = new ecsPatterns.ApplicationLoadBalancedFargateService(this, 'Service', {\n  cluster,\n  taskDefinition: taskDef,\n  desiredCount: 2,\n  circuitBreaker: { rollback: true },\n  enableExecuteCommand: true,\n  healthCheckGracePeriod: Duration.seconds(120),\n  assignPublicIp: false,\n});\n\nservice.targetGroup.configureHealthCheck({\n  path: '/actuator/health',\n  healthyThresholdCount: 2,\n  unhealthyThresholdCount: 3,\n  interval: Duration.seconds(30),\n  timeout: Duration.seconds(10),\n});\n\nconst scaling = service.service.autoScaleTaskCount({ minCapacity: 2, maxCapacity: 10 });\nscaling.scaleOnCpuUtilization('Cpu', { targetUtilizationPercent: 70 });\nscaling.scaleOnMemoryUtilization('Memory', { targetUtilizationPercent: 80 });\n```\n\n## Worker Service (No ALB, Processes SQS)\n\n```typescript\nconst workerTaskDef = new ecs.FargateTaskDefinition(this, 'WorkerTaskDef', {\n  memoryLimitMiB: 2048, cpu: 1024,\n});\nworkerTaskDef.addContainer('Worker', {\n  image: ecs.ContainerImage.fromEcrRepository(repo, props.imageTag),\n  logging: ecs.LogDrivers.awsLogs({ logGroup: workerLogGroup, streamPrefix: 'worker' }),\n  environment: { QUEUE_URL: queue.queueUrl },\n  command: ['java', '-jar', 'app.jar', '--worker'],\n});\nqueue.grantConsumeMessages(workerTaskDef.taskRole);\n\nnew ecs.FargateService(this, 'Worker', {\n  cluster, taskDefinition: workerTaskDef,\n  desiredCount: 1,\n  enableExecuteCommand: true,\n  circuitBreaker: { rollback: true },\n});\n```\n\n## Dockerfile (Java, Optimized)\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM gradle:8.5-jdk21 AS build\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY build.gradle settings.gradle ./\nCOPY gradle ./gradle\nRUN gradle dependencies --no-daemon || true\nCOPY src ./src\nRUN gradle bootJar --no-daemon\n\nFROM amazoncorretto:21-alpine\nRUN addgroup -S app && adduser -S app -G app\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=build /app/build/libs/*.jar app.jar\nUSER app\nEXPOSE 8080\nHEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=5s --retries=3 --start-period=60s \\\n  CMD wget -qO- http://localhost:8080/actuator/health || exit 1\nENTRYPOINT [\"java\", \"-XX:+UseG1GC\", \"-XX:MaxRAMPercentage=75.0\", \\\n  \"-XX:+ExitOnOutOfMemoryError\", \"-jar\", \"app.jar\"]\n```\n\n## Amazon MQ (RabbitMQ)\n\nUse when: AMQP required, migrating from on-prem RabbitMQ, complex routing (topic exchanges, headers, DLX).\n\nFor AWS-native: use SQS, SNS, or EventBridge instead.\n\n### Java Spring Boot Client\n\n```java\n// Producer\n@Service\npublic class OrderEventProducer {\n    private final RabbitTemplate rabbitTemplate;\n    public void publish(Order order) {\n        rabbitTemplate.convertAndSend(\"order-exchange\", \"order.created\", order);\n    }\n}\n\n// Consumer\n@RabbitListener(queues = \"order-processing-queue\")\npublic void handle(Order order, Channel channel, @Header(AmqpHeaders.DELIVERY_TAG) long tag) throws IOException {\n    try {\n        processOrder(order);\n        channel.basicAck(tag, false);\n    } catch (RetryableException e) {\n        channel.basicNack(tag, false, true);  // requeue\n    } catch (Exception e) {\n        channel.basicNack(tag, false, false); // to DLX\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## DOs and DONTs\n\n| DO | DON'T |\n|----|-------|\n| Use Fargate unless specific EC2 needs | Over-engineer with EC2 |\n| Use ARM64 (20% cheaper) | Default x86 |\n| Set `circuitBreaker: { rollback: true }` | Crash-loop broken images |\n| Set `healthCheckGracePeriod` 60-120s for Java | Kill containers during startup |\n| Use `enableExecuteCommand: true` | SSH into containers |\n| Use specific image tags | Use `latest` in production |\n| Set `-XX:MaxRAMPercentage=75.0` | Hardcode `-Xmx` |\n| Use `ecs.Secret` for sensitive env vars | Plain env vars for passwords |\n\n## Typical Mistakes\n\n1. **Java OOM**: Container 1024MB but Java uses host memory. Use `-XX:MaxRAMPercentage=75.0`.\n2. **Health check kills during startup**: Set `startPeriod` and `healthCheckGracePeriod`.\n3. **NAT Gateway costs**: ~$32/month each + data. Use 1 for dev, VPC endpoints for AWS services.\n4. **Deployment stuck**: New tasks fail health check, old stay. Enable circuit breaker.\n5. **Can't pull image**: Missing `ecr:GetAuthorizationToken`, or no NAT/endpoint to ECR.\n",
