            path: 'references/cdk-and-cloudformation.md',
            role: 'reference',
            content:
                "# CDK & CloudFormation Reference\n\n## CloudFormation Template Structure\n\n```yaml\nAWSTemplateFormatVersion: '2010-09-09'\nDescription: My infrastructure\n\nParameters:\n  Stage:\n    Type: String\n    AllowedValues: [dev, staging, prod]\n\nConditions:\n  IsProd: !Equals [!Ref Stage, prod]\n\nResources:\n  MyTable:\n    Type: AWS::DynamoDB::Table\n    DeletionPolicy: Retain\n    Properties:\n      TableName: !Sub '${Stage}-my-table'\n      BillingMode: PAY_PER_REQUEST\n      AttributeDefinitions:\n        - { AttributeName: pk, AttributeType: S }\n        - { AttributeName: sk, AttributeType: S }\n      KeySchema:\n        - { AttributeName: pk, KeyType: HASH }\n        - { AttributeName: sk, KeyType: RANGE }\n\nOutputs:\n  TableArn:\n    Value: !GetAtt MyTable.Arn\n    Export:\n      Name: !Sub '${Stage}-TableArn'\n```\n\n### Key Intrinsic Functions\n\n```yaml\n!Ref Resource               # Resource ID or parameter value\n!GetAtt Table.Arn           # Resource attribute\n!Sub '${Stage}-resource'    # String substitution\n!Join ['-', [a, b]]         # Join\n!If [IsProd, 3, 1]          # Conditional\n!ImportValue 'shared-vpc'   # Cross-stack\n```\n\n### CloudFormation Pros/Cons\n\n| Pros | Cons |\n|------|------|\n| Native AWS support | Verbose |\n| Rollback on failure | Slow iteration |\n| Drift detection | No loops, limited logic |\n| Change sets | Hard to refactor |\n\n---\n\n## CDK (TypeScript)\n\n### CDK vs CloudFormation\n\n| Feature | CDK | CloudFormation |\n|---------|-----|----------------|\n| Language | TypeScript, etc. | YAML/JSON |\n| Abstraction | L1, L2, L3 | L1 only |\n| Type safety | Full | None |\n| Testing | Unit tests | cfn-lint |\n| Loops/Logic | Native | Limited |\n\n### Project Structure\n\n```\nmy-service/\n├── bin/app.ts\n├── lib/\n│   ├── stacks/\n│   │   ├── api-stack.ts\n│   │   ├── database-stack.ts\n│   │   └── monitoring-stack.ts\n│   └── constructs/\n│       └── resilient-lambda.ts\n├── src/handlers/\n├── test/\n├── cdk.json\n└── package.json\n```\n\n### Entry Point\n\n```typescript\n// bin/app.ts\nconst app = new App();\nconst stage = app.node.tryGetContext('stage') || 'dev';\nconst env = { account: process.env.CDK_DEFAULT_ACCOUNT, region: process.env.CDK_DEFAULT_REGION };\n\nconst db = new DatabaseStack(app, `${stage}-Db`, { env, stage });\nconst api = new ApiStack(app, `${stage}-Api`, { env, stage, table: db.table });\nnew MonitoringStack(app, `${stage}-Mon`, { env, stage, functions: api.functions });\n```\n\n### Stack Pattern\n\n```typescript\nexport interface DatabaseStackProps extends StackProps { stage: string; }\n\nexport class DatabaseStack extends Stack {\n  public readonly table: dynamodb.Table;\n\n  constructor(scope: Construct, id: string, props: DatabaseStackProps) {\n    super(scope, id, props);\n    this.table = new dynamodb.Table(this, 'Main', {\n      partitionKey: { name: 'pk', type: dynamodb.AttributeType.STRING },\n      sortKey: { name: 'sk', type: dynamodb.AttributeType.STRING },\n      billingMode: dynamodb.BillingMode.PAY_PER_REQUEST,\n      pointInTimeRecovery: true,\n      removalPolicy: props.stage === 'prod' ? RemovalPolicy.RETAIN : RemovalPolicy.DESTROY,\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Reusable Construct\n\n```typescript\nexport class ResilientLambda extends Construct {\n  public readonly function: lambdaNode.NodejsFunction;\n  public readonly dlq: sqs.Queue;\n\n  constructor(scope: Construct, id: string, props: ResilientLambdaProps) {\n    super(scope, id);\n    this.dlq = new sqs.Queue(this, 'DLQ', { retentionPeriod: Duration.days(14) });\n    this.function = new lambdaNode.NodejsFunction(this, 'Fn', {\n      entry: props.entry,\n      runtime: lambda.Runtime.NODEJS_20_X,\n      architecture: lambda.Architecture.ARM_64,\n      memorySize: props.memorySize || 256,\n      timeout: props.timeout || Duration.seconds(30),\n      deadLetterQueue: this.dlq,\n      tracing: lambda.Tracing.ACTIVE,\n      bundling: { minify: true, sourceMap: true, externalModules: ['@aws-sdk/*'] },\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Unit Testing\n\n```typescript\nimport { Template, Match } from 'aws-cdk-lib/assertions';\n\ntest('creates DynamoDB with correct schema', () => {\n  const app = new App();\n  const stack = new DatabaseStack(app, 'Test', { stage: 'test', env: { account: '123', region: 'us-east-1' } });\n  const template = Template.fromStack(stack);\n\n  template.hasResourceProperties('AWS::DynamoDB::Table', {\n    KeySchema: [\n      { AttributeName: 'pk', KeyType: 'HASH' },\n      { AttributeName: 'sk', KeyType: 'RANGE' },\n    ],\n    BillingMode: 'PAY_PER_REQUEST',\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### Environment Config Pattern\n\n```typescript\nconst configs: Record<string, StageConfig> = {\n  dev: { logRetention: 7, lambdaMemory: 256, desiredTasks: 1, removalPolicy: 'destroy' },\n  staging: { logRetention: 14, lambdaMemory: 512, desiredTasks: 2, removalPolicy: 'retain' },\n  prod: { logRetention: 30, lambdaMemory: 1024, desiredTasks: 3, removalPolicy: 'retain' },\n};\n```\n\n### CDK Commands\n\n```bash\ncdk bootstrap aws://ACCOUNT/REGION    # first time\ncdk synth -c stage=dev                # generate template\ncdk diff -c stage=dev                 # preview changes\ncdk deploy -c stage=dev --all         # deploy\ncdk deploy -c stage=prod --require-approval broadening\ncdk destroy -c stage=dev --all        # destroy\ncdk list -c stage=dev                 # list stacks\n```\n\n### DOs and DONTs\n\n| DO | DON'T |\n|----|-------|\n| Use L2 constructs | Use L1 (Cfn*) unless necessary |\n| Use `.grant*()` for permissions | Manual IAM when grant exists |\n| Pass resources via constructor props | Use `Fn.importValue` |\n| Create reusable constructs | Copy-paste definitions |\n| Pin CDK versions | Use `*` versions |\n| Write unit tests | Deploy untested stacks |\n| Use `-c stage=dev` for env config | Hardcode values |\n| Keep stacks focused | One mega-stack |\n\n### Typical Mistakes\n\n1. **Circular dependency**: Stack A ↔ Stack B. Use SSM parameters.\n2. **Logical ID change**: Rename construct → resource replaced → data lost.\n3. **Stack too large**: 500 resource limit, 51KB template limit. Split stacks.\n4. **`cdk destroy` deletes data**: Use RemovalPolicy.RETAIN.\n5. **Missing context**: `tryGetContext()` returns undefined. Provide defaults.\n",
