            content:
                '# Debugging & AWS CLI Reference\n\n## Authentication\n\n```bash\naws configure --profile myproject-dev\nexport AWS_PROFILE=myproject-dev\naws sso login --profile myproject-dev\naws sts get-caller-identity\n```\n\n## Debugging Flowcharts\n\n### Lambda Issues\n\n```\nError? → Check CloudWatch logs\n  → Permission denied? → Check IAM role → simulate-principal-policy\n  → Timeout? → Check memory, check downstream calls, check VPC config\n  → OOM? → Increase memory, check @maxMemoryUsed in REPORT logs\n  → Throttled? → Check reservedConcurrentExecutions, request limit increase\n  → Cold start slow? → Check VPC, check package size, consider provisioned concurrency\n```\n\n### ECS Issues\n\n```\nTask not starting? → describe-tasks → check stoppedReason\n  → "CannotPullImage" → Check ECR permissions, NAT/VPC endpoint\n  → "OutOfMemory" → Increase task memory, check -XX:MaxRAMPercentage\n  → "HealthCheckFailed" → Check health check path, increase startPeriod\n  → "Essential container exited" → Check logs in CloudWatch\n\nDeployment stuck? → describe-services → check events\n  → New tasks failing health check → Check grace period, app startup time\n  → Circuit breaker triggered → Check image tag, app logs\n```\n\n### SQS Issues\n\n```\nMessages not processing? → Check event source mapping → list-event-source-mappings\n  → Mapping disabled? → Check DLQ overflow, Lambda errors\n  → Messages going to DLQ? → Check visibility timeout vs Lambda timeout\n  → Duplicate processing? → Check reportBatchItemFailures, add idempotency\n```\n\n### CDK Deploy Issues\n\n```\nDeploy failed? → describe-stack-events → find FAILED resource\n  → "already exists" → Resource created outside CDK, import or rename\n  → "limit exceeded" → Check service quotas\n  → "circular dependency" → Split stacks, use SSM\n  → Rollback stuck → delete stack with --retain-resources\n```\n\n## CLI Commands by Service\n\n### CloudFormation / CDK\n\n```bash\n# Stack events (find failure reason)\naws cloudformation describe-stack-events --stack-name STACK | head -100\n\n# Stack outputs\naws cloudformation describe-stacks --stack-name STACK --query \'Stacks[0].Outputs\'\n\n# Delete stuck stack\naws cloudformation delete-stack --stack-name STACK --retain-resources ResourceId\n```\n\n### Lambda\n\n```bash\n# Invoke\naws lambda invoke --function-name FN --payload \'{"key":"val"}\' \\\n  --cli-binary-format raw-in-base64-out out.json && cat out.json\n\n# Config\naws lambda get-function-configuration --function-name FN\n\n# Event source mappings\naws lambda list-event-source-mappings --function-name FN\n\n# Concurrency\naws lambda get-function-concurrency --function-name FN\n```\n\n### DynamoDB\n\n```bash\n# Get item\naws dynamodb get-item --table-name TBL \\\n  --key \'{"pk":{"S":"USER#123"},"sk":{"S":"PROFILE"}}\'\n\n# Query\naws dynamodb query --table-name TBL \\\n  --key-condition-expression "pk = :pk AND begins_with(sk, :p)" \\\n  --expression-attribute-values \'{":pk":{"S":"USER#123"},":p":{"S":"ORDER#"}}\'\n\n# Describe\naws dynamodb describe-table --table-name TBL\n\n# Consumed capacity\naws dynamodb query --table-name TBL \\\n  --key-condition-expression "pk = :pk" \\\n  --expression-attribute-values \'{":pk":{"S":"USER#123"}}\' \\\n  --return-consumed-capacity TOTAL\n```\n\n### SQS\n\n```bash\n# Queue attributes\naws sqs get-queue-attributes --queue-url URL --attribute-names All\n\n# Send test message\naws sqs send-message --queue-url URL --message-body \'{"test":true}\'\n\n# Receive (inspect)\naws sqs receive-message --queue-url URL --max-number-of-messages 10 \\\n  --wait-time-seconds 5 --attribute-names All\n\n# DLQ depth\naws sqs get-queue-attributes --queue-url DLQ_URL \\\n  --attribute-names ApproximateNumberOfMessages\n\n# Purge\naws sqs purge-queue --queue-url URL\n\n# Redrive from DLQ\naws sqs start-message-move-task --source-arn DLQ_ARN\n```\n\n### CloudWatch Logs\n\n```bash\n# Tail (real-time)\naws logs tail /aws/lambda/FN --follow --since 10m\n\n# Filter\naws logs tail /aws/lambda/FN --filter-pattern "ERROR"\n\n# Logs Insights\naws logs start-query \\\n  --log-group-name /aws/lambda/FN \\\n  --start-time $(date -d \'1 hour ago\' +%s) \\\n  --end-time $(date +%s) \\\n  --query-string \'filter level="ERROR" | stats count() by errorMessage\'\n\naws logs get-query-results --query-id QUERY_ID\n```\n\n### CloudWatch Alarms\n\n```bash\n# Alarms in ALARM state\naws cloudwatch describe-alarms --state-value ALARM\n\n# Metric data\naws cloudwatch get-metric-statistics \\\n  --namespace AWS/Lambda --metric-name Errors \\\n  --dimensions Name=FunctionName,Value=FN \\\n  --start-time $(date -d \'1 hour ago\' -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S) \\\n  --end-time $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S) \\\n  --period 300 --statistics Sum\n```\n\n### ECS\n\n```bash\n# List services\naws ecs list-services --cluster CLUSTER\n\n# Describe (check events for deployment issues)\naws ecs describe-services --cluster CLUSTER --services SVC\n\n# List tasks\naws ecs list-tasks --cluster CLUSTER --service-name SVC\n\n# Stopped task reason\naws ecs describe-tasks --cluster CLUSTER --tasks TASK \\\n  --query \'tasks[0].{status:lastStatus,reason:stoppedReason,exit:containers[0].exitCode}\'\n\n# Force redeploy\naws ecs update-service --cluster CLUSTER --service SVC --force-new-deployment\n\n# ECS Exec\naws ecs execute-command --cluster CLUSTER --task TASK \\\n  --container app --interactive --command /bin/sh\n```\n\n### S3\n\n```bash\naws s3 ls s3://BUCKET/prefix/ --recursive\naws s3 cp s3://BUCKET/key ./local\naws s3 sync ./dist s3://BUCKET/static --delete\naws s3 presign s3://BUCKET/key --expires-in 3600\naws s3api get-bucket-policy --bucket BUCKET\n```\n\n### SSM\n\n```bash\naws ssm get-parameter --name /prod/app/key --with-decryption\naws ssm get-parameters-by-path --path /prod/app/ --recursive --with-decryption\naws ssm put-parameter --name /dev/app/flag --value "true" --type String --overwrite\n```\n\n### IAM Debugging\n\n```bash\naws sts get-caller-identity\naws iam simulate-principal-policy \\\n  --policy-source-arn arn:aws:iam::123:role/MyRole \\\n  --action-names s3:GetObject \\\n  --resource-arns arn:aws:s3:::bucket/key\naws sts decode-authorization-message --encoded-message MSG\n```\n',
