            content:
                "# Architecture Patterns & Production Checklist\n\n## Common Serverless Architecture\n\n```\n              API Gateway\n                  │\n              Lambda (TS)  ────►  DynamoDB\n                  │\n              EventBridge\n             ┌────┼─────┐\n         Lambda  SQS   Lambda\n        (notify) │     (analytics)\n              Lambda\n             (worker)\n```\n\n## Common ECS Architecture\n\n```\n                 ALB\n            ┌─────┴─────┐\n        ECS Task     ECS Task\n        (Java API)   (Java API)\n            │\n    ┌───────┼───────┐\n DynamoDB   S3     SQS\n                    │\n               ECS Worker\n```\n\n## Error Handling Strategy\n\nEvery async path must have:\n```\nProducer → Queue → Consumer\n               ↓ (after maxReceiveCount failures)\n           DLQ ← Alarm (threshold=0)\n               ↓\n        Investigation / automated redrive\n```\n\n## Idempotency Pattern\n\n```typescript\nasync function ensureIdempotent(key: string, ttlMin = 60): Promise<boolean> {\n  try {\n    await docClient.send(new PutCommand({\n      TableName: IDEMPOTENCY_TABLE,\n      Item: { pk: key, ttl: Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + ttlMin * 60 },\n      ConditionExpression: 'attribute_not_exists(pk)',\n    }));\n    return true; // new — process\n  } catch (e: any) {\n    if (e.name === 'ConditionalCheckFailedException') return false; // duplicate — skip\n    throw e;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Service Selection Guide\n\n| Need | Service |\n|------|---------|\n| Simple async processing | SQS + Lambda |\n| Fan-out (1 event → N consumers) | SNS + SQS |\n| Complex event routing | EventBridge |\n| Real-time streaming | Kinesis |\n| API backend (light) | Lambda + API Gateway |\n| API backend (heavy/Java) | ECS Fargate + ALB |\n| Background worker | ECS Fargate (no ALB) |\n| File storage | S3 |\n| Key-value/document store | DynamoDB |\n| Config/secrets | SSM Parameter Store / Secrets Manager |\n| AMQP/RabbitMQ protocol | Amazon MQ |\n\n## Cost Pitfalls\n\n| Resource | Cost | Mitigation |\n|----------|------|------------|\n| NAT Gateway | $32/month + $0.045/GB | Use 1 for dev, VPC endpoints |\n| Kinesis (provisioned) | $0.015/shard/hour | Use ON_DEMAND |\n| DynamoDB (provisioned, no auto-scale) | Wasted capacity | Use PAY_PER_REQUEST or auto-scale |\n| CloudWatch Logs (no retention) | $0.03/GB stored forever | Set retention |\n| Lambda in VPC | Slower cold starts | Only if needed |\n| Fargate x86 vs ARM | 20% premium | Use ARM64 |\n\n## Production Readiness Checklist\n\n### Reliability\n- [ ] Every Lambda has a DLQ\n- [ ] Every DLQ has a CloudWatch alarm (threshold = 0)\n- [ ] Every async flow is idempotent\n- [ ] `reportBatchItemFailures: true` on all SQS event sources\n- [ ] ECS has circuit breaker with rollback\n- [ ] Health check grace period set for Java services\n- [ ] Lambda timeout < SQS visibility timeout / 6\n\n### Observability\n- [ ] Log groups have retention set (not infinite)\n- [ ] Structured JSON logging everywhere\n- [ ] Alarms: errors, throttles, queue depth, DLQ, ECS CPU/memory\n- [ ] CloudWatch dashboard per service\n\n### Security\n- [ ] No `*` in IAM resource policies\n- [ ] S3 BlockPublicAccess enabled\n- [ ] Secrets in SSM SecureString or Secrets Manager\n- [ ] ECS secrets use `ecs.Secret`, not plain env vars\n\n### Data\n- [ ] DynamoDB production tables: RemovalPolicy.RETAIN\n- [ ] S3 production buckets: versioned + RemovalPolicy.RETAIN\n- [ ] Point-in-time recovery enabled on DynamoDB\n- [ ] TTL configured for temporary data\n\n### Deployment\n- [ ] CDK unit tests pass\n- [ ] `cdk diff` reviewed before production deploy\n- [ ] Specific image tags (not `latest`) for ECS\n- [ ] `--require-approval broadening` for prod deploys\n",
